  "text": "Another wok that exploits various image priors during the training phase of a deep CNN [CITATION_1] is called SCRNN-Pr. One aspect of prior information focuses edge/texture restoration and the other concentrates on gradual upscaling via parallel structure recurrence. The authors claim efficient training speed along with better image quality par rapport the state of the art. Strangely enough, despite the claim of SRCNN-Pr, the same first author has not even alluded to SRCNN-Pr as a reference method, in his later related works [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] ; all the other state of the art method, he relied on for comparison, are there.",
